[[Image:Aron von Kangeq Tupilak.jpg|thumb|"Tupilak, woman and man" by Aron]]
'''Aron of Kangeq''' (born in [[Kangeq]] on April 9, 1822; died March 12, 1869) was a [[Greenland]] [[Inuit]] hunter, painter, and [[Oral history|oral historian]]. His woodcuts and watercolors are noted for their depiction of Inuit culture and history, and the often violent encounters between Inuit and Danish colonizers. His storytelling is known to children's literature in Greenland.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=3UHTsUmt1PEC&pg=PA32 Historical dictionary of the Inuit By Pamela R. Stern, pg 32], [[Google Books]]</ref><ref>http://www.bloomsburyauctions.com/detail/NY002/185.0{{dead link|date=October 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>[http://www.greenland.com/en/about-greenland/kultur-sjael/kunst/aron-fra-kangeq.aspx Aron fra Kangeq], Greenland.com</ref>

